text: The fish ball noodle I had was worth the money at $4. Other than the noodle store, there's a Muslim stall and economic rice as well. 3 food stalls and lots of empty seats on a Monday. Overall, a good place for a casual kopitiam lunch
Not many choices of food. Only a Mixed rice store, Chicken Rice and Claypot Delights store
